    "abstract": "<jats:title>Abstract</jats:title>\n                <jats:p>Testing 68 RT-PCR-confirmed COVID-19 cases and controls from Benin, Western Africa with commercially available SARS-CoV-2 antibody ELISAs revealed up to 25% false-positive results, likely due to unspecific antibody responses elicited by acute malaria. Serologic tests must be carefully evaluated to robustly assess SARS-CoV-2 spread and immunity in tropical regions.</jats:p>",
